## Keeper's Devotion
*3rd-level Way of the Vigil feature*

You gain proficiency in the Religion skill, and you can use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence (Religion) checks. In addition, you always know how much time remains before the next sunrise or sunset.

## Warding Palm
*6th-level Way of the Vigil feature*

When an ally you can see within 5 feet of you takes damage from an attack, you can spend 1 ki point as a reaction to reduce that damage by an amount equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die + your Wisdom modifier + your proficiency bonus.

## Devoted Casting
*6th-level Way of the Vigil feature*

When you use your action to cast a Way of the Vigil spell of 1st level or higher, you can spend 1 ki point as part of that action to steel yourself with the rite, gaining temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus multiplied by the level of the spell slot expended.

*This interacts with the optional Ki-Fueled Attack class feature from Tasha's Cauldron of Everything.*

## Unyielding Watch
*11th-level Way of the Vigil feature*

The range of your Warding Palm increases to 15 feet, and you can move up to 10 feet toward the protected creature as part of the reaction, without provoking opportunity attacks.

## Eternal Vigil
*17th-level Way of the Vigil feature*

Your watch does not waver, and honeyed words find no purchase. You are immune to being charmed or frightened, and magic can't put you to sleep. In addition, when you finish a long rest, you gain the benefits of the *death ward* spell.

